            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Rose Weiner (1908-1995) was a nurse with the American Medical Bureau to Aid Spanish Democracy in Spain (AMB) during the Spanish Civil War. The images in this collection were collected by Weiner in a family scrapbook. The collection includes images of Weiner’s family and friends, AMB volunteers, and the daily life of soldiers in the Spanish Civil War.</abstract>
            <origination label="creator">
                <persname source="naf">Weiner, Rose</persname>
            </origination>
        </did>
        <custodhist id="ref4">
            <head>Provenance</head>
            <p>The Rose Weiner Photograph Collection was separated from a scrapbook donated to the Abraham Lincoln Brigade Archives by Gerrie Karasik in 1996. This scrapbook collection came to New York University in January 2001 as part of the original acquisition of Abraham Lincoln Brigade Archives collections, formerly housed at Brandeis University. Manuscript material from the scrapbook can be found in the Rose Weiner Papers, ALBA #116.</p>
        </custodhist>
        <accessrestrict id="ref5">
